usage: mcp.py [-h] [--add ADD] [--categories CATEGORIES [CATEGORIES ...]]
              [--list] [--category CATEGORY] [--search SEARCH]
              [--delete DELETE] [--update UPDATE] [--url URL]
              [--activate ACTIVATE] [--deactivate DEACTIVATE] [--bootstrap]
              [--check] [--index INDEX] [--index-suite] [--server]

MCP Link Library - The Librarian

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --add ADD             Add a new link
  --categories CATEGORIES [CATEGORIES ...]
                        Categories for the link
  --list                List active links
  --category CATEGORY   Filter listing by category
  --search SEARCH       Search links
  --delete DELETE       Delete link by ID
  --update UPDATE       Update link ID (requires --url or --categories)
  --url URL             New URL for update
  --activate ACTIVATE   Activate link by ID
  --deactivate DEACTIVATE
                        Deactivate link by ID
  --bootstrap           Bootstrap the Git-Packager workspace
  --check               Check for sibling tool presence
  --index INDEX         Index a local directory
  --index-suite         Index Nexus Suite (Observer/Injector) data
  --server              Run in MCP Server mode

Commands (what they do):
  mcp-librarian --add <url>         Add a URL
  mcp-librarian --list              List active links
  mcp-librarian --search <query>    Search stored links
  mcp-librarian --index <dir>       Index a local directory
  mcp-librarian --index-suite       Index suite data (Observer/Injector)
  mcp-librarian --server            Run as stdio MCP server (injectable)
